## Lesson 1 - Basics

- Code runs from top to bottom
- Variables are containers to store info in | can be a string "your text here" , numbers 12345 , boolean true/false
- Functions only run when called

## Example
```lua
playerName = "Maxedmoto"    -- Variable to use in code: playerName -> the info = a Players name: Maxedmoto (string because of the "")

function myName()           -- function creates a function and then give it a name you want
   print(playerName)        -- code wihin a function / what will do function do when its called | when called prints the variable playerName (must exist)
end                         -- don't forget the end at the end ;)

myName()                    -- This calls the function above. (prints: Maxedmoto)


Output:

Maxedmoto

